docs.abstract: The retailer fell victim to the eroding power of shopping malls and said it would cease operations in 40 countries and close up to 178 stores in the U.S.
docs.snippet: The retailer fell victim to the eroding power of shopping malls and said it would cease operations in 40 countries and close up to 178 stores in the U.S.
docs.lead_paragraph: Forever 21, the California retailer that helped popularize fast fashion in the United States with its bustling stores and $5 tops, said on Sunday night that it would file for bankruptcy, a sign of the eroding power of shopping malls and the shifting tastes of young consumers.

headline.main: Forever 21 Bankruptcy Signals a Shift in Consumer Tastes

docs.abstract: The United States said it would impose tariffs after the World Trade Organization gave it permission to tax as much as $7.5 billion of European exports.
docs.snippet: The United States said it would impose tariffs after the World Trade Organization gave it permission to tax as much as $7.5 billion of European exports.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration said Wednesday that it would impose tariffs on European aircraft, French wine and cheese, Spanish olive oil and other goods starting Oct. 18, after the World Trade Organization granted the United States permission to tax as much as $7.5 billion of European exports annually.

headline.main: U.S. to Tax European Aircraft, Agriculture and Other Goods
headline.print_headline: European Food And Airplanes Face U.S. Tariffs

docs.abstract: The European Court of Justice said the landmark privacy law cannot be enforced beyond the European Union.
docs.snippet: The European Court of Justice said the landmark privacy law cannot be enforced beyond the European Union.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Europe’s highest court limited the reach of the landmark online privacy law known as “right to be forgotten” on Tuesday, restricting people’s ability to control what information is available about them on the internet.

headline.main: ‘Right to Be Forgotten’ Privacy Rule Is Limited by Europe’s Top Court
headline.print_headline: Decision Limits Europe’s ‘Right To Be Forgotten’

docs.abstract: The nonprofit behind the app, which relays broadcast feeds online, claims the networks have colluded in an effort to shut it down.
docs.snippet: The nonprofit behind the app, which relays broadcast feeds online, claims the networks have colluded in an effort to shut it down.
docs.lead_paragraph: Locast, a little-known nonprofit behind a free streaming service, sued ABC, NBC, CBS and Fox on Friday, alleging that the television networks colluded in an effort to chill its business.

headline.main: Locast, a Free Streaming Service, Sues ABC, CBS, NBC and Fox
headline.print_headline: Locast, a Streaming Service, Sues ABC, CBS, NBC and Fox

docs.abstract: Apps like Flo and Clue are shifting from just tracking your health data to using it to make evaluations about your health risks. Their tools may not always be accurate.
docs.snippet: Apps like Flo and Clue are shifting from just tracking your health data to using it to make evaluations about your health risks. Their tools may not always be accurate.
docs.lead_paragraph: Flo and Clue, two popular period-tracking apps, recently introduced health tools that evaluate a woman’s risk for the hormonal imbalance known as polycystic ovary syndrome.

headline.main: Period-Tracking Apps Say You May Have a Disorder. What if They’re Wrong?
headline.print_headline: Apps Parse Data to Point to Health Risks

docs.abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign sent Facebook a letter about a false video ad that a super PAC ran on the social network.
docs.snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign sent Facebook a letter about a false video ad that a super PAC ran on the social network.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A 30-second video ad that ran on Facebook this week falsely accused former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. of blackmailing Ukrainian officials to stop an investigation of his son.

headline.main: Biden Escalates Attack on Facebook Over False Political Ads
headline.print_headline: Biden Takes Facebook  To Task Over False Ad

byline.original: By Cecilia Kang and Mike Isaac

docs.abstract: Facebook’s Libra project led Beijing to accelerate its efforts. The government could soon know a lot more about how people are spending.
docs.snippet: Facebook’s Libra project led Beijing to accelerate its efforts. The government could soon know a lot more about how people are spending.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — When Facebook announced plans this year for a cryptocurrency called Libra, it said its goal was to reinvent money for the internet age. What the company probably didn’t imagine was that its efforts might spur China to get there first.

headline.main: China’s Cryptocurrency Plan Has a Powerful Partner: Big Brother
headline.print_headline: It’s Not Bitcoin. It’s Big Brother.

docs.abstract: The Federal Reserve’s rate cuts have buoyed stocks, but the economy shows signs of a slowdown. What should an investor do?

docs.lead_paragraph: Stocks have been even more fickle than usual.

headline.main: How to Invest When the Market Can’t Make Up Its Mind

docs.abstract: Men dominate monetary policy. But the Fed, E.C.B. and Bank of England are discussing ways to promote more women.
docs.snippet: Men dominate monetary policy. But the Fed, E.C.B. and Bank of England are discussing ways to promote more women.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — The European Central Bank might seem an unlikely place to hold a conference on gender equality. Or it might be exactly the kind of place that needs to.
